da georgia illinois indiana kentucky louisiana maryland mississippi missouri new jersey north carolina ohio pennsylvania south carolina tennessee and virginia founded in princeton indiana in  hhgregg was headquartered in indianapolis indiana its retail products included video products comprising televisions as well as dvd recorders home appliances such as refrigerators ranges dishwashers freezers washers and dryers and other products and services including audio hardware mattresses computers and other selected consumer electronics and accessories the company announced on november   that they would begin selling popular gaming systems such as wii xbox  and playstation  hhgregg reported an annual revenue of us  billion in fiscal year  on march   hhgregg filed for chapter  bankruptcy the filing followed the decision to close  unprofitable locations outside of its core markets troubles for hhgregg continued and it was announced on april   that it would also close all of its other stores  more than the  previously announced closings in the coming months and would lay off about  people contents  history  bankruptcy  fine lines  stock  sponsorships  references  external links historyedit an hhgregg retail store in florida in  a small storefront was erected by henry harold and fansy gregg on the north side of indianapolis the new store featured home appliances such as washing machines clothes dryers refrigerators and grills shortly thereafter they began selling televisions and other electronics map of hhgregg stores in the us in august  in  jerry w throgmartin began working in his grandfathers store while attending middle school he eventually worked his way through many positions there over the next  years and in  took over his fathers position as chairman ceo and director of hhgregg appliances and electronics dennis l may succeeded throgmartin as hhgreggs president and chief executive officer on february   and throgmartin was named executive chairman of the board throgmartin died in january  despite market trends that have diminished profit margins on hightech devices throgmartin and may expanded the business to  stores in  states as of october  throgmartin said weve been fortunate in that the areas of the overall ce business that have been strong are the areas in which we excel highend largescreen flatpanel tvs and home theater and higherend appliances on july   the company announced that it planned to open  stores in the following year primarily in richmond virginia tampa florida and in memphis tennessee many of them being in buildings formerly occupied by defunct circuit city as part of an aggressive growth strategy to fill the gap created by circuit citys bankruptcy in december  construction began on several stores in the central and eastern parts of pennsylvania the first in the state march  brought the openings of the first stores in the norfolkvirginia beach metro area in converted circuit city and linens n things locations in spring  the company expanded into the youngstown ohio market with the opening of a store in the youngstown suburb boardman ten stores opened in july  in south florida along the east coast from miami to west palm beach an hhgregg in hanover maryland opened in  in a former circuit city location in the fall of  hhgregg opened several stores in former circuit city locations in maryland and virginia also in late  hhgregg partnered with the cellular connection a cellular phone wholesaler based out of indianapolis to roll out kiosks to sell verizon wireless productscitation needed in march  hhgregg announced it would open a new location in myrtle beach south carolina also in the location of a defunct circuit city in june  hhgregg expanded into the pittsburgh market with the opening of four stores in the pittsburgh metropolitan area on september    new stores opened in the chicago area as well in september  hhgregg opened four stores in the st louis missouri metropolitan area in august  hhgregg made its debut in wisconsin by opening stores in appleton brown deer greenfield green bay and racine in november  it entered louisiana with stores in the new orleans metropolitan area and in baton rouge the companys motto was greggs got it in february  may resigned as ceo and robert riesbeck was named interim ceo in august  riesbeck was named the permanent ceo bankruptcyedit on march   hhgregg filed for chapter  bankruptcy the filing followed the closure of  unprofitable locations outside of its core markets however after failing to find a buyer after entering chapter  the company announced on april   that it would close all  of its locations the  stores previously announced to be closing plus the other  locations and lay off about  people liquidating the company all stores were closed permanently on may   fine linesedit fine lines was a division of hhgregg that was introduced november   each of its ten stores offered over  square feet  m of premium lines of appliances products and brands vary by location there were eleven fine lines locations stockedit hhgregg had its initial public offering on july   at us and is traded on the new york stock exchange under the ticker symbol hgg on february   it was announced that the nyse suspended trading of hgg in preparation for delisting sponsorshipsedit on december   hhgregg signed as one of  founding corporate partners for the lucas oil stadium home of the nfls indianapolis colts hhgreggs deal earned them rights to advertise in the south gate and display many of their large flat panel televisions the south gate is also home to a new squarefoot  m hhgregg showroom in late  to when the company closed hhgregg sponsored several drivers on the andretti autosport team they sponsored carlos muñoz and marco andretti they were slated to become the full time sponsor of andretti in  and sponsored them at st petersburg but when the company closed the team removed their logos on their cars but remained on the firesuits when takuma sato won the  indianapo