erators washers and dryers computers gaming consoles digital cameras gps navigators and mattresses the company also offers installation and tech services founded in  indianapolisbased hhgregg had expanded from southern states to the midwest and midatlantic regions in early  the company filed for chapter  bankruptcy protection and was forced to liquidate its assets after failing to secure a buyer it ceased operations in may  bankruptcy in april  after failing to find a buyer hhgregg was forced to liquidate its assets the company closed all  of its stores and ceased operations in may  in its chapter  filing the retailer listed assets and liabilities of up to  affiliate gregg appliances listed assets and liabilities from  million to  million in a separate filing at the time of its bankruptcy filing the company had been in business for  years operations home appliances represent more than half of sales with consumer electronics generating more than a third the size of hhgregg stores average around  sq ft by comparison best buy stores average about  sq ft geographic reach hhgregg operates stores in alabama delaware florida georgia illinois indiana kentucky louisiana maryland mississippi missouri new jersey north carolina ohio pennsylvania south carolina tennessee virginia west virginia and wisconsin florida with  stores is the retailers largest market followed by ohio with  and illinois and pennsylvania with  each the company can reach customers around the country through its website financial performance the hhgreggs revenue has dropped since  and in  ended march it fell below the  billion mark landing at  billion revenue was  lower than in  the company had lower samestore sales in  as sales of consumer electronics decreased it sold fewer units of tvs although many of them had bigger screen sizes and more features than previous years the retailer reduced its loss to about  million in  from about  million in  by cutting selling general and administrative costs which included lower labor costs the company also saved by increasing routing efficiency for deliveries and lower fuel prices cash outflow reached  million in  compared to cash flow from operations of about  million in  strategy hhgregg is giving its customers more opportunities to buy from it through a multichannel strategy it calls storedoor service customers can buy in store or online and pick up the item in a store or have it delivered the company has expanded its onlineonly product line and added mobile phone apps and an online financing application process it has invested in upgrading its it infrastructure to enhance its selection of appliances hhgregg has rolled out fine lines departments in a number of its stores fine lines display ultrapremium appliance brandssubzero bosch and asko for example that arent sold in hhgregg stores it had fine lines in  stores at the end of its  year and planned to open more than a dozen in  the company reworked the layout of  stores in  to better display its wares in a more visually appealing manner as well as to show product functionality furniture and appliance displays were placed in prominent spots in the front of stores hhgregg planned to redesing as many as  stores before the holiday selling season  show less  show full description  show less  show full history  show less  show all competitors amazoncom inc best buy co inc costco wholesale corporation interbond corporation of america j c penney company inc kmart corporation lowes companies inc rs legacy corporation sears roebuck and co target corporation walmart stores inc  show less  show all company news and press releases hhgregg bankruptcy kerp approved bankrupt company news fri jul  court approves hhgregg incentive program inside indiana business mon jul  hhgregg inc nysehgg files an k departure of directors or certain officers election of directors appointment of certain officers compensatory arrangements of certain officers market exclusive mon jul  hhgregg inc k  departure 